ncrete, fundamental physical “stuff” of the universe. Starting with simple mechanical models, Albert methodically constructs the defining features of quantum mechanics from scratch. He shows how the entire history of our familiar, three-dimensional universe can be discerned in the wave function’s intricate pattern of ripples and whorls. A major new work in the foundations of physics, A Guess at the Riddle is poised to transform our understanding of the basic architecture of the universe.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPhysical laws. 0aPhysicsxPhilosophy. 0aQuantum theory. 0aReality. 0aSpace. 0aWave functions. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  abell’s theorem.  abohmian mechanics.  aclassical.  aconfiguration space.  aelectrodynamics.  aepr paradox.  afunctionalism.  afundamentality.  ageneral relativity.  agrounding.  agrw.  ahamiltonian.  amany worlds Interpretation.  anewtonian.  anon locality.  aprimitive ontology.  arutherford.  aspecial.  asuperposition.  auniverse.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074970040uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674294837?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674294837423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674294837/original  a978-3-11-074970-0  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a97